description:
I'm trying to use this code to append a file into a GridFS 

  pathname = "/%s/%s" % (unique_id, key)
  d = {
      "_id":pathname
      ,"filename":pathname
      ,"contentType":v.type
      ,"metadata":{
          "filename":v.filename
          ,"field":key
          }
      }
  f = gridfs.GridFile(d, db, "w", "files")

But I got an exception on f = gridfs.GridFile(d, db, "w", "files")

  File "/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages/pymongo-0.11.3-py2.5-macosx-10.5-i386.egg/gridfs/grid_file.py", line 97, in __init__\n    self.__erase()
  File "/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages/pymongo-0.11.3-py2.5-macosx-10.5-i386.egg/gridfs/grid_file.py", line 106, in __erase\n    grid_file = self.__collection.files.find_one(self.__id)
  File "/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages/pymongo-0.11.3-py2.5-macosx-10.5-i386.egg/pymongo/collection.py", line 273, in find_one\n    for result in self.find(spec, limit=-1, _sock=_sock):
  File "/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages/pymongo-0.11.3-py2.5-macosx-10.5-i386.egg/pymongo/collection.py", line 334, in find\n    raise TypeError("spec must be an instance of dict")


Then, it works removing the _id from d dict:

  d = {
      "filename":pathname
      ,"contentType":v.type
      ,"metadata":{
          "filename":v.filename
          ,"field":key
          }
      }

The Python driver always uses {query : {...}} for queries, and the db commands for sharding don't handle this:

{"bad cmd": {"query": {"listshards": 1}}, "ok": 0.0, "errmsg": "no such cmd"}
{"bad cmd": {"query": {"netstat": 1}}, "ok": 0.0, "errmsg": "no such cmd"}
{"bad cmd": {"query": {"addshard": "www.example.com"}}, "ok": 0.0, "errmsg": "no such cmd"}

and so on.  It's making working on the sharding UI... difficult.

Code for this was:
admin_cmd = connection.admin['$cmd']

print json.dumps(admin_cmd.find_one({'listshards' : 1}))
print json.dumps(admin_cmd.find_one({'netstat' : 1}))
print json.dumps(admin_cmd.find_one({'addshard' : "www.example.com"}))

If username or password is non-ascii, problems happend during _password digest.  I am submitting a fix soon.  

    def _password_digest(self, username, password):
        """Get a password digest to use for authentication.
        """
        if not isinstance(password, types.StringTypes):
            raise TypeError("password must be an instance of (str, unicode)")
        if not isinstance(username, types.StringTypes):
            raise TypeError("username must be an instance of (str, unicode)")

        md5hash = _md5func()
        md5hash.update(username + ":mongo:" + password)
        return unicode(md5hash.hexdigest())

It is worth checking the other clients as well to ensure they all handle this the same
